              <span id="reviewTextContainer119576546" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17250019979606440024">Of all books I&apos;ve abandoned, this is one of the ones I&apos;ve put down most quickly. The writing style seemed so clumsy and pretentious to me that I simply couldn&apos;t endure it. I probably lasted the second half of how far I did because of a vague suspicion that there was quickly coming an &quot;end quote&quot; or some such mechanism because it was *so* bad that I thought I must have been being put on in some way. This literally is of a quality that if I was handed it by a high school student I could only respo</span>
  <span id="freeText17250019979606440024" style="display:none">Of all books I've abandoned, this is one of the ones I've put down most quickly. The writing style seemed so clumsy and pretentious to me that I simply couldn't endure it. I probably lasted the second half of how far I did because of a vague suspicion that there was quickly coming an "end quote" or some such mechanism because it was *so* bad that I thought I must have been being put on in some way. This literally is of a quality that if I was handed it by a high school student I could only respond with a lecture about writing in your own voice and not trying to sound literary.</span>
