<div id="review_2848590973" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2848590973" />
    <a title="Tina Rae" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1438155-tina-rae"><img alt="Tina Rae" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1626372466p2/1438155.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2848590973?book_show_action=true">Jun 17, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tina Rae" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tina Rae" href="/user/show/1438155-tina-rae">Tina Rae</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780802125934" href="/book/show/30358480-leaving-las-vegas">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1438155-tina-rae?shelf=book-club">book-club</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1438155-tina-rae?shelf=readers-choice">readers-choice</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2848590973" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1850644978159976389">Okay so. This is one of the hardest books I have ever read. But it is also the best book about alcoholism I have ever read. And for that, I am glad to have read it.<br/><br/>This book is less than 200 pages but it&apos;s a hard two hundred pages. Because it deals with a lot of really heavy subject matter. But it&apos;s also a really in depth look at two different lifestyles: prostitution and alcoholism. And it&apos;s a really raw, hard look at both of those lifestyles. It leaves nothing out and gives a really great depi</span>
  <span id="freeText1850644978159976389" style="display:none">Okay so. This is one of the hardest books I have ever read. But it is also the best book about alcoholism I have ever read. And for that, I am glad to have read it.<br /><br />This book is less than 200 pages but it's a hard two hundred pages. Because it deals with a lot of really heavy subject matter. But it's also a really in depth look at two different lifestyles: prostitution and alcoholism. And it's a really raw, hard look at both of those lifestyles. It leaves nothing out and gives a really great depiction of both of those lifestyles.<br /><br />So this book is honestly really well written and you do find yourself enjoying it. Or as much as you can enjoy a book like this. But, at the same time, books like this need to be written. Because unless you've been immediately affected by alcoholism, you probably don't know anything about it. I didn't. I honestly haven't really had much experience with addiction and books like this are how people like me learn.<br /><br />But just know that the last ten pages of this book are one of the most difficult things I've ever read. It was well written but it just hurt my soul. Because I wanted there to be another way. Even though I knew early on exactly how this would end, I wanted another way.<br /><br />So I do recommend this book. Because I think this is the type of book that needs to exist. It needs to be here to spread awareness. Because sometimes you just don't know what other people are going through and how they're living. And this book is a good description of that. So know that it will be a really hard read but I definitely do recommend!</span>
  <a data-text-id="1850644978159976389" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


