<div id="review_3992883539" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3992883539" />
    <a title="Ville Verkkapuro" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/66329259-ville-verkkapuro"><img alt="Ville Verkkapuro" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1585897470p2/66329259.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3992883539?book_show_action=true">May 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ville Verkkapuro" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ville Verkkapuro" href="/user/show/66329259-ville-verkkapuro">Ville Verkkapuro</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781611855210" href="/book/show/35286951-leaving-las-vegas">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3992883539" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13038700376901592178">I had to give this nasty book five stars because it had something very special in it. Beautiful scenery and awful, awful characters. Such moral and world-view that you can&apos;t find anywhere else. A prostitute meets an alcoholic, driven to end his life through reckless drinking.<br/>The story is unfortunately also very close to me as I&apos;ve witnessed first hand this exact story unfolding before my very eyes. I tried to get some sense of it, but with no success. Well, I guess there&apos;s as many reasons to dri</span>
  <span id="freeText13038700376901592178" style="display:none">I had to give this nasty book five stars because it had something very special in it. Beautiful scenery and awful, awful characters. Such moral and world-view that you can't find anywhere else. A prostitute meets an alcoholic, driven to end his life through reckless drinking.<br />The story is unfortunately also very close to me as I've witnessed first hand this exact story unfolding before my very eyes. I tried to get some sense of it, but with no success. Well, I guess there's as many reasons to drink as there are alcoholics in the world. <br />I've seen the film based on this book previously and it's very nice. Elisabeth Shue is absolutely gorgeous and Nicolas Cage is truly horrible, which is the way it should be.<br />This differed from the film in the best possible way, following the tone and the events, but with different emphasis and rhythm.<br />The language in this book was one of the most ambitious that I've encountered in a book. I thought my english was strong, but there was many, many new words and terms. They added a level of grandiosity to the nastiness. If this would've written like Bukowski writes, it would've been totally different. There were some neon lights and polished surfaces in this book, but the dirt and the desperation was still present on every page.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13038700376901592178" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
