<span id="freeTextContainer18050683000870795952">I only give this book three stars because I liked it enough. O&apos;Brien&apos;s craftsmanship is brilliant. His writing is experimental without overkill. If you read this with the expectation of it being a steamy romance novel, though, you&apos;ll be deeply disappointed. This book speaks more to themes of agency than anything else. For anyone who is interested, I say go ahead and pick it up, but understand that this is an emotionally heavy read. </span>
