  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/191773740" />
    <a title="Matt" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1230643-matt"><img alt="Matt" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/191773740?book_show_action=true">Jul 29, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Matt" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Matt" href="/user/show/1230643-matt">Matt</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer191773740" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7325300446736865934">I think what amazes me is the number of times I have referenced or quoted this book. It is the most remarkably sad, depressing story that is still a love story, in some strange world. Unlike most books, the movie does a good job with this one and is probably more depressing b/c you see what is going on. Only read if you like dark movies or books. But if you do, this is the book for you.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


